[name]
check_ldaps

[info]
Tests connections to an LDAPS server.
[why]
To see that the LDAPS server is working. This can be used to check for example Windows Active Directory servers.
[how]
By connecting to the LDAPS server. You can specify protocol version, password and diffrent search criterias. You can also set thresholds on responstime.
[platforms]
Not platform dependent.


